HEADWORD: Fortnight
<hw>Fort"night`</hw> <pr>(?; <it>in</it> U.S. <it>often</it> ?;
277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Contr. fr. <ets>fourteen nights</ets>,
our ancestors reckoning time by nights and winters; so, also, <ets>seven
nights</ets>, <ets>sennight</ets>, a week.]</ety> <def>The space of
fourteen days; two weeks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fortnightly</ent>⟦br⟧
